@Node ControlConfig "Fortis: Control configuration"

@{u}@{fg shine}Control configuration@{fg text}@{uu}

The Fortis game allows to use one of two default control methods which can be
activated in options menu. Each control method can be modified so a user can
configure keyboard and mouse in the game.

Config files of two control methods are in drawer "settings" (located in
the Fortis main drawer):
 - "control0.asc"
 - "control1.asc"

They are ASCII text files which can be edited in a simple text editor.

Format the files is very simple:

@{fg fill}FUNCTION@{fg text} @{fg shine}VALUE@{fg text}
@{fg fill}FUNCTION@{fg text} @{fg shine}VALUE@{fg text}
@{fg fill}FUNCTION@{fg text} @{fg shine}VALUE@{fg text}
...

@{"List of control functions" link ControlFunctions} in the game 
(@{fg fill}FUNKCJA@{fg text} in config file).

@{"List of values of control functions" link ControlValues} (keyboard and mouse) in the game
(@{fg shine}WARTO¦Æ@{fg text} in config file).

@{"Example" link DefaultControlConfigFile} of control configuration file (default first control
method in the Fortis).


